{{pp-semi|small=yes}} '''Felching''' is a [[Human sexual activity|sexual practice]] involving the act of orally sucking [[semen]] out of the [[Human anus|anus]] of one's partner. The act of sucking semen out of a [[vagina]] is known as [[Creampie (sexual act)|creampie eating]].
==Earliest appearance of the term==
According to the 2003 draft entry for "felch" in the ''[[Oxford English Dictionary]]'', the earliest occurrence of the word in print appears to have been in ''The Argot of the Homosexual Subculture'' by Ronald A. Farrell in 1972.<ref>{{cite journal | last = Farrell | first = Ronald A. | title = The Argot of the Homosexual Subculture | journal = Anthropological Linguistics | volume = 14 | issue = 3 | pages = 97–109 | publisher = The Trustees of Indiana University | date = March 1972 | jstor = 30029496 | issn = 0003-5483}}</ref>
{{cquote|FELTCH {{sic}} (v.): To use one's mouth or tongue on the anus of his partner; analingus or male cunnilingus (syn. RIM).}}
The word was subsequently featured in a 1975 [[underground comic]]: ''Felch Cumics'', published by [[Keith Green (art)|Keith Green]]. Contributors to ''Felch'' included ''[[Zap Comix]]'' cartoonists [[Robert Williams (artist)|Robert Williams]], [[S. Clay Wilson]], [[Robert Crumb]], and [[Spain Rodriguez]]. Members of the ''Zap'' collective had previously published two sexually themed comic books, ''Snatch'' and ''Jiz'', and decided to continue pushing the envelope by publishing ''Felch''. According to Williams:
{{cquote|OK, since we didn’t get in any trouble with ''Snatch'' and ''Jiz'', and a couple of these other comics, I was partying one night with Crumb, Wilson and these other guys. And Wilson mentioned to me, he says, "I was talking to Ken Weaver and he had this real interesting word." I said what, "What is it?" "A word called 'felch.'" I said, "What does that mean?" He said, "It is a real old term and it means orally withdrawing semen from someone’s lower digestive tract after having anal sex." I said, "There’s a word for something like that?" That’s incredible that not only is there a word like that, but it has a provenance. Hell yeah, we’re going to do a felch comic. So I talked to Crumb, "Yeah, we’re going to do a felch comic."}}
Crumb's contribution was a parody of an [[editorial cartoon]] featuring [[John Q. Public]] felching "[[Mother Nature]]/[[Liberty (goddess)|Lady Liberty]]" after she has had anal sex with a ''[[Pravda]]''-style cartoon capitalist.<ref>{{cite book |last=Crumb |first=R. |authorlink=Robert Crumb |title=The Complete Crumb Comics, Volume 10: Crumb Advocates Violent Overthrow |publisher=Fantagraphics Books |date=March 1994 |isbn=1-56097-137-1 |at=p. 64, reproduction of cartoon from ''Felch Cumix'' 1975 |editor1-last=Thompson |editor1-first=Mark |editor2-last=Groth |editor2-first=Gary |edition=1st |location=Seattle, Washington }}</ref> Williams' contribution to the comics was titled "The Nectar of Satan."<ref name="englishdotufldotedu-imagetext-archive-williams"> {{cite web |url=http://www.english.ufl.edu/imagetext/archives/v1_1/williams/ |title=Robert Williams, 'Underground(s)' |author=Robert Williams |publisher=[[Donald Ault#ImageTexT|ImageTexT: Interdisciplinary Comics Studies]] |accessdate=2006-12-02 |authorlink=Robert Williams (artist) }}</ref>
It was also used in 1979 by [[Larry Kramer]] in his novel [[Faggots (novel)|''Faggots'']], where he defined it as sucking the ejaculate from the anus after intercourse.<ref>Kramer, L. (1979) ''Faggots''. New York: Grove Press.</ref>
